<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colorful Activities to Mark HK Return to Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 170 programs of
celebration will be staged here between late June and early July
to mark the return of Hong Kong to the motherland, which falls on
July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong people can either catch a glimpse of the festivity on
the scene or watch various programs to be televised live on
circuit, said Raymond Wu, chairman of the committee for
celebrating Hong Kong's return to China -- a body specially
founded to organize and coordinate non-governmental activities of
celebration.
</P>
<P>
At a news briefing today, Wu said the eve of the handover will
be highlighted by a carnival in Victoria Park, a spectacular
performance at the Happy Valley race course and a television
special at the Hong Kong Cultural Center in Kowloon.
</P>
<P>
On July 1, hundreds of domestic and overseas musicians, singers
and film stars will perform at the Reunification Gala to be held
at the 25,000-seat Hong Kong Coliseum. At the same time, a
spectacular fireworks and laser display will light up the sky over
the Victoria Harbor, which links the Kowloon Peninsula and Hong
Kong Island.
</P>
<P>
A float parade will take place on the main streets on the Hong
Kong Island on July 2, also a public holiday. And on the following
day, a week-long music festival will begin, featuring a variety
of programs by local and international artists. Starting from
late June, a seven-day exhibition highlighting scientific
cooperation between China's inland areas and Hong Kong will be
opened at the City University.
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan, vice-chairman of the committee, said: "Through all
these activities, we want to convey a message to Hong Kong
residents that reunification is a matter that needs participation
from all of us. We should make joint efforts to create a new era."
</P>
<P>
The total expenditure of these events would not exceed 80
million HK dollars (about 10 million U.S. dollars), which the
committee has already raised.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
