<HEADLINE> Spain's King Ends Visit to Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 7 (Xinhua) -- King Juan Carlos I of Spain has left
Moscow after a three-day state visit to Russia, the Itar-Tass news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the king met with Russian President Boris
Yeltsin to discuss bilateral economic cooperation and other
bilateral and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Juan Carlos also spoke in the Russian Chamber of Commerce and
Industry and met Patriarch of Moscow and All Russia Alexy II.
</P>
<P>
Both sides were satisfied with the visit, giving fresh impetus
to good relations between the two countries in either the economic
or the political sphere.
</P>
<P>
King Juan Carlos I arrived in Moscow Monday for a state visit
at the invitation of Yeltsin. 
</P>
