<HEADLINE> HK University to Offer Courses on Basic Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Center for Professional and
Continuing Education of the Hong Kong Polytechnic University will
offer a special series of courses including the Basic Law, and the
Chinese language in July and August to meet new learning needs.
</P>
<P>
The center will offer two courses to afford the public a means
to learn more about the Basic Law. The course Hong Kong's Basic
Law for business executives will focus on discussing those
sections of the Basic Law which relate to the business sector.
</P>
<P>
Four new courses on the business in the Chinese mainland will
also be launched in the series such as investment in securities in
the Chinese mainland, China shares -- fundamentals and investment
strategies, successful negotiation plan for joint ventures in the
mainland and application of Yin Yang and Five Elements to
personnel management.
</P>
<P>
Together with three other existing courses, the courses aim at
equipping business personnel with solid and practical knowledge of
the Chinese business arena. Prominent academics from universities
in the Chinese mainland will be invited to lecture on some of
these courses.
</P>
<P>
The other three existing courses on offer are property in the
Chinese mainland -- investment and sales, taxation for foreign
investors -- a practical approach and China's economic laws for
foreign investors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
