<HEADLINE> Hang Seng China Enterprises Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Hang Seng China Enterprises Index
today rose 32.88 points to close at 1,143.43.
</P>
<P>
The Index, introduced in August 1995, tracks the overall
performance of China's 25 state enterprises listed on the Hong
Kong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile today's Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index rose 9.66 points
from the previous session to close at 1,911.29.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index comprises 50 most actively-traded
stocks of middle capitalization companies on the local bourse to
help investors and fund managers diversify their portfolios.
</P>
<P>
The two segmented Hang Seng indices are devised by Hang Seng
Index (HSI) Services Limited, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Hang
Seng Bank. 
</P>
