<HEADLINE> Israel Urged to End Occupation of Palestinian Territories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Israel must stop all actions that
change the status of the city of Jerusalem, including
expropriation of land and properties, a Chinese international
issue expert said here today.
</P>
<P>
Israel had no right to declare Jerusalem to be its capital,
said Yang Guang, Deputy Director General of Beijing's Institute
for West Asian and African Studies, at the United Nations Asian
Seminar and NGO (Non-Governmental Organization) Symposium on the
Question of Palestine.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Palestinian people have the inalienable right
to return to their homes and properties from which they have been
displaced and uprooted.
</P>
<P>
Yang said the only way to solve the question of Palestine is to
fully respect the Palestinian people's inalienable rights.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians began to be displaced from their homeland in
the first Middle East war in 1948 and in 1967 when their
territories were occupied by Israel.
</P>
<P>
U.N. agencies had estimated that about 1.1 million Palestinians
have become refugees as the direct results of the two wars, and
the number does not take into account the natural demographic
growth of the refugees. The refugees live in their neighboring
countries like Jordan, Lebanon and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, held from may 5 to 7, is under the auspices of the
U.N. in cooperation with the Indonesian Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Among the 200 participants of the seminar were representatives
from Asian countries and the United Nations, foreign ambassadors
to Indonesia and representatives from Indonesia's universities and
Asian NGOs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
