<HEADLINE> Malaysian PM Awarded S.Africa's Highest Honour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad today became the first head of government to be awarded South
Africa's highest honour, the Order of Good Hope: Class I Grand Cross
(gold), said a source reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir, arrived in the country earlier today from Botswana, was
bestowed the Order of Good Hope by South African President Nelson
Mandela for his personal contribution to the promotion of the
bilateral relations between the two countries, said the source.
</P>
<P>
A large Malaysian business and Foreign Ministry delegation and
several South African cabinet ministers attended the brief investiture
ceremony at the Presidential Office in Cape Town.
</P>
<P>
The honour is usually conferred on heads of state and in special
circumstances to heads of government, said a presidential aide.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir became the 27th recipient since Mandela's inauguration in
1994, joining several heads of state such as Queen Elizabeth II,
French Presidents Francoise Mitterand and Jacques Chirac, Robert
Mugabe of Zimbabwe, and Samora Machel of Mozambique who received the
honour posthumously last October.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia has become South Africa's fourth largest foreign investor
and major trading partner within three years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
