<HEADLINE> Toddlers Hospitalized After Eating Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Three toddlers in Florida were
hospitalized after eating crack cocaine they found on a bedroom
floor.
</P>
<P>
The mother of two of the children was arrested and charged with
possession of cocaine and three counts of child neglect.
</P>
<P>
"It's frustrating," the Associated Press quoted police Lt.
Brian Humm as saying. "Sometimes you think you've seen it all and
then something like this happens."
</P>
<P>
Tia Brown called 911 Tuesday to report that her two children,
Tiarra McKenzie, 8 months, and Albert McKenzie Jr., 1, and their
cousin, Shanti Merant, 3, had eaten the drug.
</P>
<P>
Authorities said that after calling 911, Brown flushed some
cocaine down the toilet and refused to tell police exactly how
much cocaine was in the house.
</P>
<P>
The children were in serious condition Tuesday at a hospital in
West Palm Beach where their stomachs were pumped. 
</P>
</TEXT>
