<HEADLINE> Macao Starts Course on Basic Law for Teachers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Macao started a special course on
Tuesday to brief school teachers the Basic Law of Macao so that
they can better teach students on the subject.
</P>
<P>
Around 40 teachers from 10 middle schools, all teaching the
course of the basic law, attended the course in their spare time.
</P>
<P>
"The course will help them understand more accurately (the
basic law) and grasp the main spirits and contents of the law,"
said Lau Sin Peng, secretary-general of the Chinese Education
Association of Macao, which co-sponsored the one month-course.
</P>
<P>
"They will be able to convey the basic law to students more
comprehensively, systematically and profoundly," she addressed at
a brief opening of the course.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of Macao middle schools have course on the basic law,
which was promulgated in 1993. A special textbook on the law was
published two years ago and adopted by a dozen of schools. 
</P>
</TEXT>
