<HEADLINE> Zambia's Closed Copper Mine to Re-open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chambishi Copper Mine, a major
one in Zambia which was closed in 1987, is ready to re-open.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Situs Mulenga, privatization leader for
Nchanga Division, Chambishi and Kansanshi mines of the state-owned
conglomerate Zambia Consolidated Copper Mines (ZCCM), in Kitwe,
Copperbelt Province last night, according to the Zambia News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The Chambishi mine with copper ore reserves of about 50
million tons closed in August 1987 because of financial problems.
</P>
<P>
Mulenga said that the copper ore has been graded at 2.5, its copper
ore reserve go up to 900 meter level according to a study done by
ZCCM on re-opening feasibilities in the mine.
</P>
<P>
Mulenga said all that is required is that the new owners
should equip it with new machinery.
</P>
<P>
In the current process of the ZCCM privatization, some
companies have shown interest and lined up as bidders to purchase
the mine whose infrastructure is still intact.
enditem

