<HEADLINE> Namibia Cannot Act Against Illegal Fishers, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Namibian government has no
authority to act against Namibian vessels found fishing illegally in
South African waters, a top official said in Windhoek today.
</P>
<P>
Shihaleni Ndjaba, Namibia's Acting Permanent Secretary for
Fisheries said that his ministry was aware some of the country's
vessels had been spotted in South African waters, but for the time
being no action could be taken against them.
</P>
<P>
This was due to the fact that current laws on sea fisheries did not
provide for punitive measures against such offenders, Southern
African Broadcasting Association quoted Ndjaba as saying.
</P>
<P>
But the Namibian official noted that new legislation was being
prepared under which Namibian vessels spotted in other countries'
territorial water would be fined or impounded. enditem

