<HEADLINE> Cook Talks of New Era of Good Ties Among Leading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Britain's new Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook said here today that London wished to start a new era of
cooperative relations between the leading members of the European
Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
"We're determined to draw a line under the sterile and negative
confrontation of the past," said Cook at a news conference after
talks with his German counterpart, Klaus Kinkel, this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
It was the first foreign visit by Cook since he took office
last week. Before coming to Bonn, Cook had also paid a visit to
Paris.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters in Bonn that his visit to Paris and Bonn
itself was a signal that Britain wanted to show that it was taking
Europe seriously and wished to be taken seriously within Europe.
</P>
<P>
"It's our intention that Britain should from now on be one of
those leading members of Europe, not a country on the sideline,
seeking to be obstructive to the direction of Europe. We want to
be helping to shape the direction of Europe," he said. 
</P>
