<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosion Rocks Lagos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 7 (Xinhua) -- A bomb planted at the roadside
exploded early morning today in Lagos, but causing no injuries,
the News Agency of Nigeria reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said the explosion occurred at around 7 a.m. on the
Herbert Macaulay Road in the Yaba area, ripping off the road
kerb.
</P>
<P>
Military spokesman, Emmanuel Young Arebamen described those
planted the bomb as "saboteurs". He said the bomb went off no
sooner than the military truck conveying military personnel
passed by, indicating that it was targeted at the military force.
</P>
<P>
The explosion is the sixth in seven months, the report added.
