<HEADLINE> Gaddafi Flies to Niger in Definace of Air Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NIAMEY, Niger, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi
flies to Niamey today on a one-day visit to Niger in defiance of a
U.N. air embargo imposed on it in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Gaddafi arrived here directly in a special plane of the Libyan
Arab Airlines from Tripoli, the capital of Libya, and was welcomed
by Nigerian President Ibrahim Barre Mainassara and other
government officials at the Niamey International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Gaddafi's visit to Niger was made at the invitation of Niger
and Nigeria to take part in the activities of the Muslim new Hijra
year.
</P>
<P>
This is another visit abroad by Gaddafi in defiance of the
U.N. travel ban imposed on it after Libya failed to surrender
two Libyans wanted in connection with the 1988 bombing of a Pan Am
jet that killed 270 people aboard.
</P>
<P>
In June 1996, Gaddafi flew to Cairo, the capital of Egypt, from
Tripoli to attended the Arab Summit held there.


