<HEADLINE> China Facing Heavy Unemployment Pressure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 8 (Xinhua) -- China faces heavy unemployment
pressures and the situation will last for some time, Chinese
Vice-Minister of Labor Lin Yongsan said at a news conference
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, there were 5.53 million registered
jobless persons, with unemployment standing at three
percent. Meanwhile, over 22 million employees in urban areas and
130 million in rural areas are regarded as surplus labor,
according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The rapid economic development in China can still not guarantee
adequate job opportunities for local labor, but the government is
making every effort to tackle the problem by developing labor
markets and standardizing job-agencies, Lin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
