<HEADLINE> HK Records Good Tourist Arrivals in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 8 (Xinhua) -- The total number of visitor
arrivals to Hong Kong in the first quarter of this year was 2.9
million, an increase of 9.0 percent over the same period last
year, according to statistics released today by the Hong Kong
Tourist Association (HKTA).
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that all major market regions recorded
growth over the period, with the highest coming from Taiwan, where
a rise of 25.4 percent was recorded. Arrivals from the Chinese
mainland grew by 17.0 percent, while those from Americas rose by
9.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
In March alone, arrivals rose by 8.8 percent to a total of 1.0
million, according to the statistics.
</P>
<P>
The HKTA is forecasting an increase of about six percent in
total arrivals in 1997, to a year-end total of around 12.4
million.  
</P>
