<HEADLINE> UK Legislative Program Finalized by New Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Britain's new Labor cabinet in its
first meeting today finalized a major legislative program to
enable Prime Minister Tony Blair to carry out his election
promises.
</P>
<P>
The legislation, containing more than 20 bills on education,
crime, jobs and decentralization, will be outlined in a speech to
be read by Queen Elizabeth next Wednesday when she officially
opens the first session of the parliament that was chosen at the
May 1 election.
</P>
<P>
"We have agreed the Queen's speech," Deputy Prime Minister John
Prescott told reporters at the end of the cabinet meeting.
</P>
<P>
"It reflects all those priorities that we had in the general
election," he added.
</P>
<P>
Blair aides said that the Labor government will push
legislation through parliament using its massive 179-seat
majority. 
</P>
