<HEADLINE> China Agrees to Request by Monaco to Keep Hong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 8 (Xinhua) -- China has agreed to a request by the
Principality of Monaco to keep its honorary consulate in the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region of China after July 1.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Consul General to Monaco Xie Xiehe Wednesday met with
Minister of State of the Principality of Monaco Michel Leveque in
the latter's residence.
</P>
<P>
Xie conveyed to Leveque a formal letter from the Chinese
government agreeing to Monaco's request for keeping its honorary
consulate in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The government of Monaco also organized a ceremony marking this
agreement between China and Monaco.
</P>
<P>
Leveque said at the ceremony that there exists a real
friendship between Monaco and China, and he expressed the wish
that cooperation will develop between the two countries in the
economic, trade and cultural fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
