<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets With UN Secretary-General (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji, meeting
with the United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan here today,
said that actions that depreciate, weaken, or try to bypass the
role of the UN will not work and that many global issues can not
be settled without international co-operation.
</P>
<P>
As the world marches towards multi-polarization, Zhu said, it
needs a powerful UN and, the success of the UN depends on the
active co-operation and support of its member countries.
</P>
<P>
He noted that great changes have taken place in the world
situation since the end of the cold war, providing opportunities
and tougher challenges for the UN. Any reform move of the UN
should reflect the changes and meet the demands of the time, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that there has been sound co-operation between China
and the UN and that he hopes the Secretary-General's visit will
increase that co-operation.
</P>
<P>
He said that, in the present complicated and ever-changing
situation, the role played by the UN Secretary-General is unique,
and spoke highly of Annan's ability and rich diplomatic
experience. He said he believes the UN will gain more vigor
under Annan's leadership.
</P>
<P>
Annan said he is glad to have the chance to visit China and to
gain a better understanding of China's great achievements with
his own eyes.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the UN, which faces a heavy task of reform, is
working on deciding its responsibilities for the next twenty
years. The UN appreciates China's support and contributions in the
past and expects it to have a more active role in UN affairs in
the future.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
