<HEADLINE> Hingis Looks to Be Ready for French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 8 (Xinhua) -- World women's top-ranked Martina
Hingis of switzerland says she expects to be fit for the French
Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Swiss star injured her knee falling off a horse
last month and has been forced to pull out of three tournaments
since suffering the injury on April 21.
</P>
<P>
Hingis told the French sports daily L'Equipe that she was
optimistic about making her return at the French Open starting May
26.
</P>
<P>
Hingis pulled out of last week's Rexona Cup in Hamburg, this
week's Italian Open and next week's German Open in Berlin. She
would enter the French Open without any tournament matches on clay
in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Prior to her injury, Hingis had won six titles this year,
including the Australian Open. She earned more than 1.2 million
U.S. dollars this year and became the youngest No. 1 player in
history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
