<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Kowloon Express Train Service to Start On May 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 8 (Xinhua) -- An express-train will leave
Shanghai at 8:04 on May 19 for Kowloon, according to local railway
authorities, marking the beginning of regular passenger service
between the largest economic center in China's inland areas and
Hong Kong, which is due to return to Chinese sovereignty by July 1.
</P>
<P>
The 16-car No. 99 and 100 passenger-trains have luxurious
hand-made compartments and departs Shanghai every day, but goes to
Guangzhou on odd days and Kowloon on even days. It takes 29 hours
for the journey.
</P>
<P>
Two hundred and eighty-seven staff members have been recruited
for the first Shanghai-Kowloon train and they have been given a
special training program aboard the train.  
</P>
</TEXT>
