<HEADLINE> Eleven Mafiosi Arrested in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Eleven members of the Corleone Mafia
clan were arrested today in the Sicilian capital of Palermo by the
local Anti-Mafia department.
</P>
<P>
Among the arrested was Mario Grizzaffi, a nephew of the
imprisoned Cosa Nostra boss of bosses, Salvatore Toto Rinna.
</P>
<P>
Grizzaffi allegedly participated in a number of Mafia summits
as an high-ranking member of Cosa Nostra, along with Rinna's son
Giovanni and other bosses.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said that Grizzaffi and the others arrested today
made up a "reserve unit" filling in for Mafia kingpins behind
bars such as Rinna and Leoluca Bagarella.
</P>
<P>
Palermo prosecutor Alfonso Sabella said that they will be
charged with sheltering Mafiosi on the run, storing weapons and
running a extortion racket.
</P>
<P>
Rinna was arrested in January 1993 after nearly 23 years on the
run. 
