<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has begun moving the Zairean
soldiers who fled to the country to safe places within Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Home Affairs Minister Chitalu Sampa said here on Wednesday
that "as of now, the number of refugees is fluctuating because
things in Zaire have not settled to the satisfaction of the
people, but some of them have decided to go back to their home
country."
</P>
<P>
The remaining 331 soldiers in Mansa in northern Zambia and 106
on the Copperbelt are being moved to safe places, but he did not
disclose the location.
</P>
<P>
Initially Zambia could not begin the exercise because of
meagre resources but are now in the process of getting support
from World Vision International, Red Cross and the United Nations
High Commission for Refugees for the exercise.
</P>
<P>
Since the civil war began in Zaire in October 1996, a large
number of Zaireans including soldiers have fled to Zambia.
</P>
