<HEADLINE> Mongolia Simplifies Entry Procedures for Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Foreign travelers to Mongolia
will no longer be required to submit an invitation letter for
visa application as long as their stay in the country lasts no
more than 30 days.
</P>
<P>
Under the new regulations effective from May 1, 1997,
foreigners who intend to stay in Mongolia for less than 30 days
can apply for entry visas directly at Mongolian embassies or
consulates abroad or at border ports of entry, an official of
Mongolian Ministry of External Relations said.
</P>
<P>
Thoses who plan to stay in Mongolia for more than 30 days will
have to produce an invitation letter when applying for an entry
visa.
</P>
<P>
The simplification of entry formalities is a manifestation of
Mongolia's further opening up to the outside world, the official
said.
</P>
<P>
The new regulations are not applicable to people from China,
Russia and some other nations with which Mongolia has signed
consular agreements, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the entry procedures for Chinese, Russians and
nationals from some other countries will remain as they were and
continue to be carried out according to the consular agreements.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
