<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Joint Team Fails Mount Kurlakangri Attempt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 8 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-Japanese Mountaineering team
failed to scale the 7,418-meter virgin Mount Kurlakangri and has
abandoned further attempt after a 50-meter-long gap got in the
way, captain of the Chinese side Duojifu said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Duojifu said on a phone in Luozha County of Tibet, where the
Kurlakangri Mount lies, the climbers found no way to detour after
the gap stopped them with only 400 meters down from the peak.
</P>
<P>
With time up, goods and materials running out, the frustrated
climbers had to gave up the action, which has lasted one month.
</P>
<P>
The climbers have all got back to the base camp safely and will
leave the base camp on May 13 for Lhasa, Duojifu said. 
</P>
