<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Pledges More Cooperation With Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng said
today that China and Mozambique should make greater efforts to
find new ways for cooperation on the basis of equality and mutual
benefit.
</P>
<P>
During the talks with his Mozambican counterpart, Pascoal
Manuel Mocumbi, Li said the two governments should encourage the
two countries' economically powerful enterprises with good
reputation to strengthen cooperation in compliance with
universally-accepted international practices and the law of
economy.
</P>
<P>
Both sides also agreed that there were many cooperative
opportunities for the two countries in the agricultural field,
saying that they will discuss setting up joint ventures in this
regard.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they said the international community, especially
developed countries, should make greater contributions to reducing
the debts of African countries.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi briefed Li on Mozambique's domestic situation. He said
Mozambique's society had generally been stable since peace
prevailed in the country.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the country is facing the double task of
construction and reform, thus making it imperative for Mozambique
to enhance exchanges with China in this field.
</P>
<P>
Li said China's success had proved that political stability is
critical to reform. China has been attaching great importance to
properly addressing the relations among reform, development and
stability during the course of reform and construction, Li added.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li arrived here from Lusaka on Wednesday for a two-day
official good-will visit, the third leg of his seven-nation Africa
tour beginning from May 3. He has already visited Seychelles and
Zambia before arriving here and is expected to continue his visit
to Gabon, Cameroun, Nigeria and Tanzania. 
</P>
