<HEADLINE> Syrian Newspaper Criticizes Netanyahu's Policy on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Syrian official newspaper
"Al-Thawra" today criticized severely Israeli Prime Minister
Binyamin Netanyahu's statement on rejecting withdrawal from the
Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said that Netanyahu made the statement to the
Jewish settlements officials Wednesday, reiterating his rejection
of withdrawal from the Golan Heights, and his support for
confirming the Golan Annexation Law.
</P>
<P>
Israel snatched from Syria the Golan Heights during the June 5
War in 1967 and its Knesset (parliament) adopted law annexing the
1,200 square kilometer territory.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said in a commentary that Netanyahu's statement
means a policy of "aggression and occupation" and "provocation and
intimidation" without caring about the fate of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
"Netanyahu's statements," the newspaper added, "mean that he
wants to get out of the peace process and cancel all that has been
achieved in the past years."
</P>
<P>
Al-Thawra called for an effective U.N. attitude to bring the
Israeli government back to its senses and put an end to its
revolt against the will of international legitimacy.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper also appealed to the world powers, particularly
Europe, to undertake their responsibilities and to make further
efforts to save the Middle East peace process. 
</P>
