<HEADLINE> China Opposes Sao Tome and Principe to Establish Ties With Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Shen Guofang, commenting on Sao Tome and Principe establishing
so-called diplomatic ties with Taiwan, said today that China
strongly opposes countries which have established diplomatic ties
with China setting up so-called diplomatic ties with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Shen Guofang said that Sao Tome and Principe, regardless its
traditional friendship and cooperation with China, established
so-called diplomatic relations with Taiwan. "This is a perfidious
and nearsighted move," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We strongly oppose countries which have diplomatic ties with
China establishing so-called diplomatic ties with Taiwan. There is
only one China in the world, and the government of the People's
Republic of China is the sole legal government representing the
whole of China, and Taiwan is an inalienable part of China," Shen
Guofang said.
</P>
<P>
"China's stand to safeguard the reunification of the motherland
and oppose 'two Chinas' or 'one China one Taiwan' is firm and
unshakable," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
