<HEADLINE> U.N. to Help Pakistan Obtain Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 8 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Industrial Development
Organization (UNIDO) has decided to launch a 20.87 million rupee
(about 500,000 U.S. dollars) investment and technology promotion
program to help Pakistan obtain foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The program envisages support to Pakistan in expanding its
industrial production by getting foreign investment and
technology, the Associated Press of Pakistan quoted UNIDO sources
as saying here today.
</P>
<P>
The objective would be realized through various forms of
business-oriented industrial cooperation agreements between
private and public enterprises in Pakistan and potential foreign
entrepreneurs, they said.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony of the program, the "UNIDO INTECHMART '97
Pakistan Project," will be held here on May 10 and representatives
of all the concerned agencies and the government will be present,
they said.
</P>
<P>
Investment Technology Market (INTECHMART) is the UNIDO's
promotional event to stimulate foreign investment, technology
transfer and other forms of industrial and financial cooperation
between local and foreign industrialists, said the UNIDO sources.
</P>
