<HEADLINE> Chinese Party Leader Meets Kazak Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a standing committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Party (CPC), welcomed a delegation from the
People's Unity Party (PUP) of Kazakhstan, led by its chairman
Akham Bizhanov, to Beijing this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that since China and Kazakhstan established diplomatic
ties, bilateral relations have developed smoothly through efforts
by leaders of the two sides. He said that the CPC and Chinese
government attach great importance to Sino-Kazak friendly
relations, and that China is always a reliable friend and
cooperative partner of Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Hu noted that friendly relations between the CPC and the PUP
are based on the four principles for party-to-party relations and
have created favorable conditions for a strengthening of exchanges
between the two parties, exchanging Party administration
experience, and promoting the continuous development of bilateral
good-neighborly friendship and cooperation of mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Bizhanov said that the PUP delegation is happy to have the
opportunity to visit China and conduct friendly exchanges with the
CPC, and that the exchange of visits and meetings between the two
countries' top leaders have promoted the development of bilateral
good-neighborly friendship and cooperation, which is in the
fundamental interest of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the PUP supports the consolidation and
development of bilateral friendship and cooperation, and is
willing to contribute to this end.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived here on Tuesday at the invitation of the
CPC.  
</P>
