<HEADLINE> HK Export Rises Slightly in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 8 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Hong Kong's total
exports increased marginally by 0.5 percent in February this year
over the same month last year, according to official statistics
released today.
</P>
<P>
Concurrently, the volume of imports increased by 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing January-February 1997 with January-February 1996, the
volume of Hong Kong's re-exports increased by 2.4 percent, while
the volume of domestic exports decreased by 8.0 percent. Taking
together, the volume of total exports increased by 0.8 percent,
while imports increased by 5.4 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Comparing February 1997 with February 1996, the prices of
re-exports and domestic exports decreased by 1.5 percent and 2.1
percent, respectively. Import prices fell by 2.6 percent.
</P>
