<HEADLINE> Macao Jobless Rate Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 8 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate during the first
three months of the year dropped to 3.2 percent in Macao,
according to the latest official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
show that the jobless rate declined continuously since late last
year.
</P>
<P>
It was recorded at 3.4 percent during the period between
December 1996 and February 1997, against 4.2 percent in the first
three months of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The underemployment rate remained at 0.6 percent between
January and March, the same as in the December-February period.
</P>
<P>
The department announced the figures after sample surveys
between January and March this year.
</P>
<P>
Macao economic officials said earlier that economic growth in
the territory began to pick up in late 1996, after a slowdown for
more than two years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
