<HEADLINE> Beijing-Kowloon Express Runs Soon (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The operation of the train before the handover of Hong Kong to
China on July 1 is of special significance to mark the event as
well as to facilitate the exchanges between inland areas and
Hong Kong," the official said.
</P>
<P>
"We're very optimistic about the passenger sources", he added.
</P>
<P>
Instead of the newly-built landmark Beijing-Kowloon Railway,
China's longest, the express train will first be operated on the
old Beijing-Guangzhou railway.
</P>
<P>
"Since Beijing-Guangzhou Railway is among the four trunk lines
which underwent speed-upgrading from April 1, it will ensure the
speed of the express."
</P>
<P>
"I'm sure the new Beijing-Kowloon line will be eventually used
to link with Hong Kong", he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Four kinds of commemorative tickets, in pure gold, silver,
gold-plated, silver-plated, will be issued by the
administration, it was announced.
</P>
<P>
The tickets -- 97 sets of gold and 97 sets of silver, plus 1997
gold-plated sets and 1997 silver-plated sets -- will be
auctioned by companies in Beijing and Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
