<HEADLINE> International Acrobatics Festival to Be Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 8 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Wuqiao International
Acrobatic Arts Festival will be held in Shijiazhuang, capital of
north China's Hebei Province, from November 1-7.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizers, 28 programs, about 20 from
overseas, will attend the games for three golden, six silver, and
nine bronze medals.
</P>
<P>
Acrobatic experts from both China and overseas and many
world-renowned acrobats will be invited to attend a symposium on
acrobatics.
</P>
<P>
More than 170 programs from more than 30 countries have been
staged at the biennial event, which started in 1987.
</P>
<P>
Wuqiao county, dubbed as the "cradle of acrobatics," has made
great contributions to the art of acrobatics worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
