<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Holds Talks With UN Secretary-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 8 (Xinhua) -- China will play a more active role
in and further improve the sound cooperative relations with the
United Nations, Chinese Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said during
his talks with UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan here today.
</P>
<P>
Annan arrived here for a five-day official visit to China on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During their talks in the Diaoyutai State Guesthouse, Annan
said that he was glad to visit China for the first time as
Secretary-General. He also extended condolences on the passing
away of late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Qian welcomed Annan on his first trip to China and thanked him
for his condolences.
</P>
<P>
Qian praised Annan for his persistent efforts to revitalize the
UN and strengthen its role. China believes that with the support
of all UN members, Annan will make further positive contributions
to maintaining world peace and security, promoting economic and
social development in all countries, and strengthening
international cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian, also vice-premier of the State Council, said that the
world situation is undergoing profound changes, which have not
only brought about rare opportunities for the UN, but also
enlarged its responsibilities and posed stern challenges to it.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that in the five decades after the Second World War
history has proved that the UN plays a role that cannot be
replaced by other international organizations. In the new
situation, resolution of many global problems needs the role of
the UN more than ever.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the success of the UN depends on the support
and cooperation of all members, he said.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that the UN will pay more attention to the issues
of economic and social development and make more efforts to
promote such development in the developing countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Annan agreed with China's view on the role of the UN and
thanked the Chinese government for its consistent and strong
support to the UN. He said that in the past years, China has made
significant contributions to the UN, especially by actively
participating in the UN's drive to promote economic and social
development and eliminate poverty. The UN expects that China will
play a bigger role in all fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
Annan said that as UN Secretary-General, he will continue to
uphold the UN resolutions on the Taiwan issue and stick to the
"one China" principle.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that as a permanent member of the UN Security
Council, China places importance on and supports that the UN
playing an active role in international affairs in accordance with
the aim and principles of its charter. China believes that it will
play a more active role in and further promote the sound
cooperative relations with the UN in the process of economic
development and further enhancement of national strength.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed gratitude to Annan for his adherence to the
principled stance of "one China" and the UN Charter and relevant
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of reform of the UN, Qian said that China supports
that relevant organs of the UN will carry out reform in order to
suit the changing situation and meet the demands of the times.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the reform is to reinforce the UN's capability
of safeguarding peace and promoting development, so as to
guarantee a better service for its member countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Annan agreed with China's point that the reform of the UN
should focus on economic and social progress. To this end, he
said, the UN should establish a new mechanism to give full play to
the limited loans.
</P>
<P>
To intensify the "south-south co-operation" is significant to
the issue of development, and China's experience in this regard is
worth drawing on, he said.
</P>
<P>
They also exchanged views on a broad range of international
issues, and reached common or similar views on many of them.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
