<HEADLINE> Iranian Minister Winds up Visit to Damascus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar
Velayati has stressed that Iran and Syria should exchange views to
resist Israeli aggressive policy towards Arabs, Damascus Radio
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister made the remarks to reporters
before leaving the Damascus International Airport last night,
winding up a visit of several hours to Syria.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in the Syrian capital, Velayati was received
by Syrian President Hafez al-Assad and conveyed him a message
from Iranian President Hashemi Rafsanjani, but the content of
which was not disclosed, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Assad discussed with Velayati the latest developments in the
Middle East, as well as the preparations for the summit of the
Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC), due in Tehran in
December, added the radio report.
</P>
<P>
Velayati told reporters that his talks with the Syrian
president covered issues of common concern, bilateral ties between
the two countries, Israeli attacks on south Lebanon and Israel's
policy of settlement in Jerusalem, describing the talks as
"constructive and very good."
</P>
<P>
The visit by the Iranian foreign minister to Syria came within
the framework of his current tour to a number of Arab countries to
extend to their leaders invitations from the Iranian president
to participate in the December OIC summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
