<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Stock Market Trading Stays High in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Total turnover value on the Hong
Kong Stock Exchange in April was 200.38 billion HK dollars (25.85
billion US dollars) in April, increasing by 3 percent over the
previous month.
</P>
<P>
But average daily turnover for the 22 trading days in April was
9.102 billion HK dollars (1.17 billion US dollars), a decrease of
11 percent as compared with that in March.
</P>
<P>
A total of 100.025 billion shares changed hands in April,
compared with 94.153 billion in March. The average daily turnover
by volume was 4.56 billion shares, down 8 percent from March.
</P>
<P>
Average daily turnover for the first four months of the year
was 9.846 billion HK dollars (1.27 billion US dollars), compared
with 5.572 billion HK dollars (718.96 million US dollars) in the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover by value was 797.488 billion HK dollars (102.90
billion US dollars) during the first four months of the year,
compared with 445.725 billion HK dollars (57.51 billion US
dollars) for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
During the first four months of this year, the average daily
turnover by volume was 4.734 billion shares, compared with 2.042
billion shares during the corresponding period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
A total of 383.499 billion shares were traded during the first
four months of this year, compared with 163.375 billion shares
during the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index at the end of April was 12,903.30, an
increase of 3 percent from last month and 18 percent from April
1996.
</P>
<P>
The market capitalization at the end of April 1997 was 3,580.89
billion HK dollars (462.05 billion US dollars), an increase of 36
percent over the same date last year. 
</P>
