<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 4 Wounded in Bomb Explosion in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 8 (Xinhua) -- One child was killed and four
others wounded this morning when a bomb exploded in Erzurum,
eastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the explosion broke out at an residential
area of Sivas district of Pasinler town in Erzurum at 08:55 local
time (05:55 GMT) after the bomb was brought from a military target
range in the area. But the report did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
The bomb exploded among the children, who were aged between
four and 12, said the report, adding that one of them died
immediately on the scene and the other four who had been wounded
were rushed to hospitals in Pasinler town and Erzurum for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
Security officials said that Turkish police started an
investigation into the incident, said the agency. 
