<HEADLINE> Africa Full of Hope: Chinese Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
has described Africa as a continent full of hope, which has tided
over its most difficult times and embarked on the road of
revitalization.
</P>
<P>
"The development prospect of Africa is inspiring. Any ideas
suggesting to ignore Africa, to belittle Africa or to harbor
pessimistic view about Africa's economic development is entirely
groundless," said Li Peng at a banquet given in honor of him by
Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano last night.
</P>
<P>
Africa as a whole is an important member of the international
community, Li said, adding the sustained development of the world
is inseparable from the progress of Africa while the development
of Africa will help make the international economy more
prosperous.
</P>
<P>
The 20th century has been an "emancipation century" for
Africa, Li said, believing that the 21st would be a
"development century" for Africa in which the African people would
rid themselves of poverty and march towards prosperity.
</P>
<P>
This would add a new chapter in the annals of human history,
he stated.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 20 years and more, the Sino-Mozambican friendly
and cooperative relations have stood the test of the time and
international turbulence and have been developing steadily. In
international affairs, the two countries have been sympathized with
and supported each other along with increasing cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In the new international situation, China and Mozambique should
join their efforts to further enhance friendship politically, expand
cooperation areas so as to benefit the people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In his toast, President Chissano described Li's "historic
mission" to his country as an important embodiment of renewing
the bilateral cooperation in line with new conditions of the two
countries. He also expressed his sincere thanks to China for its
enormous contribution to Mozambique's economic and social
development.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong to China is a great success of the Chinese
people, and it is also a typical example of resolving similar issues
through dialogue, Chissano said, adding that he believed the success
of the "one country, two systems" policy of the Chinese government
on the issue of Hong Kong would be conducive to the settlement of
the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
He shared Li's view for the establishment of a new, just and
equitable international economic order. Without the self-emancipation
economically, the African people would continue to rely on others
and they would still suffer from exploitation and slavery, Chissano
stressed.
</P>
<P>
What China and other Asian countries have gained in their
economic achievements has encouraged the African peoples in
building for themselves a more prosperous life, the president
said. enditem

=05080812

=05080819
NNNN
16:20 16:20 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
