<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan Developing Permaculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 8 (Xinhua) -- An example of permaculture, Cili
county in central China's Hunan province protects the environment
with forest preservation and water conservancy facilities, and
controls industrial pollution, while harnessing low-yield grain
fields.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, forest coverage reached 58 percent in Cili
county. The county also cultivated 65 square kilometers of
soil-eroded land. About 30 percent of the low-yield grain land was
transformed.
</P>
<P>
Eco-agriculture has increased agricultural output in Cili. In
the last three years, the grain output of Cili has increased by
five percent each year, and about 220,000 peasants have shaken off
poverty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
