<HEADLINE> Japan Vies to Hold Second Spot in East Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Japan is in no mood to step off from the
second spot at the medal tally while its closest rival South Korea is
to host the second East Asian Games here from May 10 to 19.
</P>
<P>
"Japan is set to retain the second place and will not surrender it
to the hosts South Korea," said Yoshiro Okai, Chef de Mission of the
Japanese delegation.
