<HEADLINE> Tourists Arrivals Increase in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in the Philippines
reached 351,569 for the first two months of this year, an increase
of 7.5 percent from 326,978 a year ago, the Department of Tourism
said today.
</P>
<P>
The top source of visitors for the period was the United States
with 62,984 which comprised 17.9 percent of the total, according
to the statistics released by the department.
</P>
<P>
Japan remained the second top source of visitors, while its
total slipped 4.4 percent to 59,685 from last year's 62,416.
</P>
<P>
Visitors from Korea, the third top source also went down by a
smaller 0.11 percent to 40,937, according to the department.
</P>
<P>
However, significant increases were recorded from fourth and
fifth sources Taiwan and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The number of visitors from Taiwan increased by 13.6 percent to
32,081 while that of Hong Kong surged 24.5 percent to 28,655.
</P>
<P>
The department pointed out that the increase in visitor
arrivals at the start of the year can be attributed to many
special festivals held by the tourism authority aimed at
attracting more tourists. 
</P>
