<HEADLINE> Muslims Urged To Develop Noble Values </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian King Tuanku Ja'afar
today urged Muslims to develop noble values to ensure harmony and
progress in the Muslim society.
</P>
<P>
Religious education and self-discipline are of utmost
importance to achieve this, the King said when addressing the
Muslim New Year (1418) rally here.
</P>
<P>
He said that without a firm sense of conviction and a strong
desire for self-discipline, social problems like gangsterism, drug
addiction and moral turpitude within Muslim families would become
rampant and weaken the Islamic Ummah.
</P>
<P>
The King said the younger Muslim generation should realize the
importance of equipping itself with useful knowledge and avoiding
involvement in any activity that would bring about its own ruin.
</P>
<P>
He wanted Malaysia's Islamisation process to be given broad
emphasis to change the pattern of life among the people who had
deviated from the true teachings.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that culture should be integrated with Islam to
ensure consistency in the country's Islamisation process.
</P>
<P>
He also reminded Muslims to believe in Allah's divine promises
that religious observances such as praying, fasting, paying the
zakat and performing the haj would be the strong bastion against
lowly despicable influences. 
</P>
