<HEADLINE> Nepali Transport Workers Call off Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 8 (Xinhua) -- A trade union of transport workers
in Nepal has called off a nation-wide strike earlier scheduled on
next Sunday and Monday, union officials here said today.
</P>
<P>
The Independent transport Workers' Association of Nepal (ITWAN)
has decided to indefinitely postpone its future agitation programs
including the next week's strike, ITWAN President Uddhav K.C.
said.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the decision came after an agreement was
reached Monday between the union and the country's transport and
labor authorities over the transport workers' demands.
</P>
<P>
The government has agreed to implement revised transport
regulations within one month, he said, adding that the workers
would resume their protest program if the government does not keep
its words.
</P>
<P>
The ITWAN has been staging agitation programs since late last
year to press the government to fulfill its 10-point demand,
including implementation of revised regulations, provision of
working licenses and increase in accident insurance.  
</P>
