<HEADLINE> South Chinese Aquatics Popular in Overseas Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANYA, May 8 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Sanya in south
China's Hainan Province has exported 300 tons of aquatic products
so far this year.
</P>
<P>
Fishermen from this city by the South China Sea rely heavily
on aquatics, but were restricted to inshore fishing due to
lagging technology in the past.
</P>
<P>
Priority was given to developing a large-scale fleet of boats
and deep-sea fishing. And the city built an ice-making factory
with a daily capacity of more than 200 tons, in a bid to store
high quality aquatic products.
</P>
<P>
Now over 3,000 tons of aquatics are sold in Sanya every
day. Conger and other seafoods of high value are exported to Japan
and Hong Kong, and even to Europe and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Some Hong Kong companies have invested millions of yuan in
setting up an aquatic product export base in the city.
</P>
<P>
The city's quarantine departments have tightened supervision
over aquatics for export, and prevented 18 tons of poor quality
conger products from being exported in March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
