<HEADLINE> Bosnian Serbs Accuse Moslems of Preparing War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Bosnian Serb army's Chief of
General Staff Pero Colic today accused Muslim forces of preparing
a massive attack on Serbian territories in Bosnia-Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
Colic made the remarks during an interview published today by
the Belgrade-based evening newspaper Vecernje Novosti.
</P>
<P>
He said reliable intelligence information suggests that the
Muslim army now is making all-round preparations for the attack on
Serbs and the occupation of Serbian territories in coming August.
</P>
<P>
The planned attack, Colic said, will mainly target the northern
strategic line, on which the city of Brcko is a crucial point, to
cut the Serbian territories into two halves in seven days.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the goal, he alleged, the Muslim army is now engaged
in intensive military training with the assistance of 250 officers
from the United States and some Islamic countries.
</P>
<P>
The Muslim forces are also stepping up espionage activities on
Serbian territories to collect intelligence information, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian side has already notified international
organizations of the situation, the army chief said, adding that
all Serbs have been urged to get ready to defend their country.
</P>
