<HEADLINE> Italy Minister Urges Withdrawal of MPF if Fino Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations should withdraw the
Multinational Protection Force (MPF) from Albania if the national
reconciliation government headed by Prime Minister Bashkim Fino
falls, Italian Defense Minister Beniamino Andreatta said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister told the Lower House that if the Fino
government fell, normal life would no longer exist in the war-torn
country. In this case, the United Nations should reconsider the
task or even withdraw the Italian-led MPF.
</P>
<P>
Italy and the other countries in the mission were seeking to
increase understanding between the Albanian parties and enable
elections to be held at the end of June, he said.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta said the MPF's most important role, as well as the
protection of aid convoys, was its presence as "an important
factor for confidence" among the Albanians.
</P>
<P>
He said the MPF's brief does not extend to policing crime gangs
or stopping Albanians leaving their country in an attempt to enter
Italy illegally.
</P>
<P>
If these tasks were accepted, he said, a more substantial force
would be needed, with different troops.
</P>
<P>
He said that at the Albanian government's request, Italian
naval forces were patroling in Albanian territorial waters to
dissuade and stop the flow of illegal immigrants
</P>
<P>
The defense minister also proposed holding an international
conference on rebuilding the Albanian economy and financial
system, following the havoc wreaked by the collapse of pyramid
financial schemes which precipitated the present crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
