<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Building Up Flower Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, the capital city of
South China's Guangdong Province, saw its flower industry grow
more than three times in production value from 1978 to last
year.
</P>
<P>
The value surged from 70 million yuan in 1978 to 230 million
last year. And flower farms expanded their growing areas by nearly
16 times from 1978 to 2,000 ha.
</P>
<P>
The city now has Guangdong Province's biggest flower
market. With research efforts increasing, the city has created
many types of new flowers and plants. Currently, it is growing
more than 1,400 types of cut flowers, pot flowers, and
plants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
