<HEADLINE> Italy to Limit Albanian Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini
said in San Marino today that Italy would sift through those
Albanians arriving in Italy to sort out illegal immigrants.
</P>
<P>
Responding to U.N. High Commission for Refugees' request on
Wednesday that Italy host as refugees of those Albanians with a
valid reason for fleeing their country, the foreign minister said
Italy would only treat as refugees who are threatened in their
security, politically or physically, not the others.
</P>
<P>
He urged international refugee officials to define what they
mean by a "refugee".
</P>
<P>
According to ANSA reports from San Marino, a small and ancient
enclave in Italy, Dini said Albania was in very difficult economic
and social conditions which some Albanians are seeking to flee
"but they are not refugees".
</P>
<P>
Dini said Italy would put a brake on those transporting
Albanians to Italy for profit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
