<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Moots Natural Rubber Producer Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka has mooted an alliance
with Malaysia and other natural rubber producing countries to
counter the stiff competition posed by synthetic rubber, according
to Minister of Trade, Commerce and Food Kingsley Wickramaratna.
</P>
<P>
The minister was quoted today by the Daily News as saying that
Sri Lanka had mooted this idea with several other rubber producing
countries and they have responded well to the proposal.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia and Indonesia in particular will figure in a big way
in the alliance as they are large producers of natural rubber, the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
The world rubber buyers have dictated the prices of natural
rubber because of the competition among producers so far. Once a
new alliance of rubber producers was formed, the prices would be
stabilized, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka is one of the main natural rubber producing countries
in the world. Its rubber production was estimated at 112 million
kgs last year.  
</P>
