<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Striving to Advance Development of Real Estate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, has implemented a series of
preferential policies to support development of the real estate
sector.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the city hopes that the move may
help establish a group of large comprehensive real estate
development enterprises by the year 2000, which will also become
the city's major tax contributors.
</P>
<P>
The preferential policies include giving tax rebates to a
number of key city- and provincial-level real estate development
groups, and giving subsidies to real estate developers who have
sold their open-market buildings at much lower prices to support
the city's "comfortable housing" project -- a program aiming at
providing low-income families with low-priced apartments.
</P>
<P>
The city will also adjust the housing construction structure
and arrange more "comfortable housing" projects to speed up
commercialization of housing for urban residents, and vigorously
expand the leasing of open-market apartments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
