<HEADLINE> Romania, Hungary Sign Accord on Border Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Romania and Hungary today signed
an accord on bilateral cooperation in the border areas.
</P>
<P>
After the signing, Nicolae Noica, Minister of Public Works and
Territorial Planning of Romania, said it is important to develop
economic and social cooperation in areas on the Romanian-Hungarian
border.
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, the two countries will cooperate in all areas
within three years along the 442-kilometer border, including
establishing new customs and maintaining the rivers across the
border.
</P>
<P>
Since the Treaty on Understanding, Cooperation and
Good-Neighborliness between Romania and Hungary was signed last
September, relations between the two countries have expanded
greatly.
</P>
<P>
In February, they signed an agreement on cooperation in
fighting organized crime, terrorist activities and drug
trafficking. In March, they signed an accord on rail and road
transport.
</P>
<P>
Trade and economic cooperation between Romania and Hungary have
developed rapidly in recent years, with the bilateral trade volume
in 1996 amounting to nearly 500 million US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
