<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Lawmakers Form Group to Oppose Joining NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, May 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 180 lawmakers today formed an
unofficial group aimed at preventing Ukraine from joining NATO.
</P>
<P>
The group, called "Ukraine outside NATO", warned in a statement
that joining the Western alliance would "pull our country into a
fratricidal war with neighboring states".
</P>
<P>
There is broad opposition to NATO membership in Ukraine. Russia
has been strongly opposing NATO's expansion toward its borders.
</P>
<P>
The new group, comprising 187 lawmakers mainly from the
Communist Party and the Socialist Party, was formed on the day
when visiting NATO Secretary-General Javier Solana handed to
President Leonid Kuchma a draft document outlining a special
partnership with the former Soviet bloc.
</P>
<P>
Like Russia, Ukraine is seeking something on paper to fend off
any security threat as Europe restructures its defense lines.
</P>
<P>
But Ukraine has been an active participant in NATO's
Partnership for Peace program. It has not announced it intends to
join NATO but Kuchma has urged closer integration with NATO and
the European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
