<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Solar Energy Development Center Built in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Construction of Qinghua Sun City,
the first production, research, and application base of solar
energy in China, has started in Beijing's suburban county of
Changping.
</P>
<P>
The 7.2 million US dollar base is the third phase of a joint
project between prestigeous Qinghua University and Beijing Glass
Instrument Factory.
</P>
<P>
With the completion of the first and second phases in 1993 and
1996 respectively, the world's largest factory of all-glass vacuum
heat concentration pipes has an annual production capacity of five
million units.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the Sun City will be completed in three
years. Three production lines are scheduled to go into operation
in early 1998, and two will produce heat concentrators with an
annual production capacity of 300,000 sq. m. and an output value
of 48.2 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The annual output value of the Sun City is expected to double
to 800 million yuan by the year 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
