<HEADLINE> Qinzhou Port on High Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Qinzhou Port of the Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region invested 50 million yuan on infrastructure last
year.
</P>
<P>
The investment was used for port railway projects, water
supply, electrical transformers, automatic telephone switching
systems, and other auxiliary facilities, including office
buildings, hotel, and trading center.
</P>
<P>
The port handled a volume of 185,000 tons of cargo. The port
registered 3.6 million yuan in revenues last year, and turned over
1.4 million yuan in taxes.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the port attracted investment of 330 million yuan
from outside, which was drawn to seven projects, including two
cargo berths. 
