<HEADLINE> Hubei to Host Yandi Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Suizhou City in central China's Hubei
Province will host a festival on June 1 to honor Yandi, one of
the traditional ancestors of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
According to historical records, Yandi, also known as Shennong,
was born on April 26 on the Chinese lunar calendar, and his
birthday falls on June 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
According to organizers, the three-day Yandi Shennong Festival
will include worshiping ceremonies, and sightseeing, cultural, and
business activities.
</P>
<P>
People from the Republic of Korea, the Philippines, Taiwan, and
Hong Kong have already applied to take part in the event, one of
the largest festivals in the province. 
