<HEADLINE> 3 More Heroin Refineries Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 8 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities have seized
three more heroin refineries in Muse area, northern Shan state of
the country last month, The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 138.8 kilograms of different grades of heroin and
liquid, 592.3 kilograms of opium, 1,542 kilograms of acetic
anhydride and other chemicals were confiscated during raids by
local army unit columns on April 23-24.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier report, over 67 kilograms of heroin
were also uncovered by the authorities in Hsenwi and Kanyan areas
in the same northern Shan state during two mopping-up operations
last month.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show altogether 11 heroin refineries have
been destroyed by the authorities in Shan state of Myanmar since
last August including nine in the northern Shan state's Kutkai,
Hsenwi and Mongko, and two in the eastern Shan state's Tachilek
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
