<HEADLINE> Ukraine Draws Armenia 1-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, Ukraine, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine was forced to a 1-1
draw in a World Cup qualifier Wednesday against Armenia.
</P>
<P>
The draw served as a blow to Ukraine's chances of making the
1998 World Cup finals in France.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine started the match strongly as midfielder Andriy
Shevchenko scored at the 6th minute off a pass from Yuriy
Dmytrulin.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine then dominated the match but failed to score again.
</P>
<P>
Armenia had only one serious challenge on the Ukrainian goal at
the 75th minute and Artur Petrosyan easily scored 15 meters from
the goal.
</P>
<P>
After the match, Ukraine leads Group 9 with 13 points from 6
games. Germany is second with 11 points from 5 matches. 
