<HEADLINE> Gabon's Trade With China Rises Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, May 8 (Xinhua) -- Gabon's trade with China rose
sharply to 189 million U.S. dollars in 1996 from 126 million
dollars a year before.
</P>
<P>
Gabon, on the west coast of Africa, is among China's top
trading partners in the continent. It exported 146 million dollars
worth of goods to China last year.
</P>
<P>
Though a small country with an area of 267,000 square
kilometers and a population of 1.3 million, Gabon is endowed with
rich resources. It has a proven oil reserve of 200 million tons, a
manganese reserve of 200 million tons, and a uranium deposit of
400 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Gabon is also noted as a "country of forest", with 80 percent
of its land being covered with forests. Timber reserves total 300
million cubic meters, including such rare woods as ebony,
cigar-box wood and sandalwood.
</P>
<P>
Its territorial waters are also an excellent fishing ground,
containing an estimated stock of 1 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Rich resources help boost the country's trade and economic
cooperation with other countries including China.
</P>
<P>
Since Gabon and China established diplomatic ties in 1974,
bilateral cooperation has been expanded to cover agriculture,
health care, fishery, education and public utilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
