<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Slovak Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting here today with Slovak Foreign Minister Pavol Hamzik, said
that China is willing to develop long-term and stable co-operation
with Slovakia in various areas.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government values its friendship with Slovakia and
hopes to expand bilateral co-operation based on the principles of
mutual respect, equality, mutual-benefit, and non-interference in
each other's internal affairs, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that in recent years, high-level contacts have
been frequent and bilateral co-operation in different sectors has
increased, and that China is satisfied with the smooth development
of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated China's belief that its economic and trade
relations with Slovakia are very important, and that it wants to
further expand this co-operation.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to encourage direct contacts between companies
and enterprises of both countries to raise bilateral economic and
trade coordination to a new stage through various kinds of
economic and technological co-operation, he said.
</P>
<P>
In conveying President Michal Kovac and Prime Minister Vladimir
Meciar's regards to Jiang, Hamzik said that a top priority item in
Slovak foreign policy is the development of friendly ties with
China, and that Slovakia pays a great deal of attention to China's
role in the Asia-Pacific region and the world and to its reforms
and opening up.
</P>
<P>
There are no problems between the two countries and bilateral
ties are sound, he said, and Slovakia hopes to further expand its
reciprocal co-operation with China in various fields. He extended
an invitation from President Kovac to Jiang. Jiang thanked him for
the invitation and said he will visit Slovakia when it is
convenient for both sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
