<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a standing committee
member of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee Political
Bureau, here today called for further reforms in the
administrative systems and structures of Chinese institutions.
</P>
<P>
He made the call while meeting with the delegates who are
attending a seminar on setting up institutions and on Deng
Xiaoping's administration management theory and reforms of
institutions. Deng, who passed away on February 19 this year, was
the architect of China's reform and opening-up drive.
</P>
<P>
