<HEADLINE> Nigeria Launches Road Vision 2000 Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria today set up a Road Vision
2000 Committee to take care of road management and financing.
</P>
<P>
The committee headed by Michael Adesina is composed of
representatives from the National Association of Chambers of
Commerce, the National Association of Road Transport Owners, the
Federal Ministry of Finance and other organizations.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the committee in Abuja, Minister of Works and
Housing Abdulkarim Adisa said the government will set up a road
fund, which will derive its seed money from road users.
</P>
<P>
Charges on road users will include fuel subsidy, toll
collection and other road related taxes, he said.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, the minister said poorly-maintained roads are
causing Nigeria a loss of 80 billion Naira (about one billion
U.S. Dollars), or 5.5 percent of the Gross Domestic Product a
year. 
</P>
