<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-07 18:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> GCC, EU to Hold Meeting on Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC) and the European Union (EU) will hold discussions on their
cooperation on May 20 in Riyadh, the capital of Saudi Arabia,
reports reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meeting is aimed to create and develop
partnership between small and medium-sized companies in the two
regional blocks, Kuwait News Agency reported, quoting a statement
issued today by Secretary General of the GCC Chambers Union
Muhammed Al-Mulla as saying
</P>
<P>
The secretary general said the small and medium-sized companies
mainly include those manufacturing foodstuff, chemicals, plastics,
industrial machines and tools.
</P>
<P>
Two working papers by the European commissioner in the GCC on
how to enter the European market and incentives provided by the
European side to the small and medium-sized GCC companies will be
discussed during the meeting, he said.
</P>
<P>
The GCC will also prepare a working paper on the atmosphere of
investment in the GCC states which is to be discussed by both
sides.
</P>
<P>
The GCC groups Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, the United Arab Emirates,
Oman, Qatar and Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
Al-Mulla said the EU is GCC's number one trade partner as trade
volume between the two blocks is at more than 35 billion
U.S. dollars annually.
</P>
<P>
Besides, GCC total investments in EU countries exceeded 150
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, Al-Mulla pointed out that there are still some
problems obstructing the development of further and comprehensive
cooperation between the two blocks.
</P>
<P>
He cited obstacles like the Gulf petrochemical carbon-tax as a
protectionist trend hindering the Gulf petrochemical exports. In
addition, the little European investments in the six GCC states
are other problems affecting the growth of cooperative
relationship.
</P>
<P>
Al-Mulla said he anticipated that the meeting will encourage
the conclusion of long-term deals between the two potential
partners.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the meeting will provide an opportunity for
the Gulf companies to develop active and serious dialog with the
European partners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
