<HEADLINE> French, German Groups Vow to Build Defense-Space Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The French Lagardere defense-media
group and the German Daimler-Benz Aerospace (DASA) aeronautics and
airspace group have vowed to build a European bloc producing
missiles, satellites and defense electronics products.
</P>
<P>
In a "strategic" agreement signed between Lagardere and DASA
Tuesday, DASA also expressed its "total and exclusive" support to
Lagardere in the latter's bidding for Thomson CSF, Europe's
largest defense electronics concern now being privatized by the
French government.
</P>
<P>
The two groups will "immediately" set up a world's third
largest airspace company baptized "Matra Marconi-DASA Dornier,"
which will have a total capital of 15 billion francs (3 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The new company, named after DASA and the Matra Marconi Space,
an airspace joint venture of Lagardere and the British GEC group,
will produce satellites, satellite-launchers, and space orbiting
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Matra Bae Dynamics group, which produces
missiles and is a joint venture of Lagardere and the British
Aerospace group, will be joined by DASA's missile producing
affiliate, the LFK.
</P>
<P>
DASA and Lagardere also agreed to further cooperation in
defense electronics industry that produces equipment systems of
command, control, communication and information. 
</P>
</TEXT>
