<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Exercises Not Against Any Country: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish-Israeli-U.S. joint
military exercises scheduled to be held this summer are not
directed against any countries in this region, a goverment
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
At a weekly press briefing, Turkish Foreign Ministry deputy
spokesman Sermet Atacanli said that the three-nation joint
military exercises are aimed for "the civil goal and the
strategic importance."
</P>
<P>
He said that the military exercises will be held in the
international waters of eastern Mediterranean Sea in the way of
the search-and-rescue scenario. But the exact date has not been
fixed, he added.
</P>
<P>
"Turkey is a country which attaches importance to the
bilateral and regional cooperation and this is one of the basic
factors of our foreign policy. The three-nation military
exercises to be held are part of our understanding", said
Atacanli.
</P>
<P>
He added: "The Israeli-Turkish-U.S. joint naval exercises will
secure contributions to the stability in the Middle East."
</P>
<P>
In order not to disturb its Arab neighbors, the Israeli
Defense Ministry has claimed that the joint military exercises
will "be of human nature and focus on search-and-rescue
scenario," and are not aimed at the two traditional Israeli
foes, Iran and Syria.
</P>
<P>
The frequent visits between senior Turkish and Israeli
high-ranking officials in recent months have caused grave concern
from Arab world, including Egypt, which obviously fears the
establishment of a Tel Aviv-Ankara alliance.
</P>
<P>
A string of senior Turkish officials, most of them from the
military, have visited Israel in a bid to further expand its
cooperation with Israel in the defense and military fields.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
