<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Holds Talks With Mozambican </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, Mozambique, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
and Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano shared the view to
further advance bilateral relations and gained common
acknowledgement on a wide-range of international issues in their
talks today.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming Li Peng's first visit to the country, Chissano
defined Chinese premier's African trip as of "extremely important
significance" and the Mozambican government and the people are
honored to host the premier's tour.
</P>
<P>
Under the new international situation, Mozambican leaders
keenly hope for exchanging views in depth with Chinese leaders on
bilateral relations and international affairs, with a view to
enhancing mutual understanding and helping push ahead the
existing friendly cooperative relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng conveyed Chinese President Jiang Zemin's regards to
President Chissano and Jiang's invitation to Chissano to visit
China. Chissano gave his reciprocal regards to President Jiang
and said he was expecting to visit China again.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng highly valued the Sino-Mozambique relationship, saying
that Sino-Mozambique friendship fostered after the independence
of Mozambique in 1975 has kept developing and the two countries
have been conducting equal and mutually beneficial economic
cooperation. "China wishes to further strengthen such a
relationship with Mozambique," Li Peng said.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng thanked the Mozambican government for its support to
China on the human rights issue in the international arena and
appreciated the Mozambican government's stand to uphold the "One
China" policy on the Taiwan issue. Chissano stressed that the
Mozambican government would continue to resolutely support China
on the human rights issue and uphold that all countries should
respect each other and oppose the imposing of pressure on others
on the issue. On the Taiwan issue, he stated, the Mozambican
government would also continue to stick to the "One China"
stance.
</P>
<P>
On the trade and economic ties between the two countries, Li
Peng said China's aid to Mozambique within its reach mirrors the
friendship of the Chinese people towards the Mozambican people.
In the new situation, the Chinese government wishes to probe new
ways and channels of economic and technical cooperation on the
basis of equality and mutual benefit. And as a matter of fact,
there is potential for further cooperation in resources
exploitation, developing agriculture and forestry by setting up
joint ventures, Li Peng said. The two governments should also
encourage their enterprises to cooperate in these areas and
establish direct links, the Chinese premier noted.
</P>
<P>
Sharing Li Peng's view in this aspect, Chissano said China had
not interrupted its aid to Mozambique even when Mozambique was at
its most difficult times. Mozambique has learned from its own
experience that there would be no economic development without a
stable political environment. Now that domestic peace has been
realized in Mozambique and the country needs all the more to
strengthen its cooperation with China as China's brotherly aid
devoid of any conditionalities, Chissano said.
</P>
<P>
Chissano said he was pleased with the effective cooperation
between the two countries in water-conservancy, and medical and
public health fields, stressing that he welcomed Chinese firms to
invest in Mozambique and carry out two-way trade and that
enterprises of the two countries should also increase exchanges
and confidence so as to expand cooperation.
</P>
<P>
After being briefed on Mozambique's domestic situation, Li
Peng congratulated the Mozambican government for the realization
of its domestic peace and national reconciliation and its efforts
to rebuild the country. Li Peng also appreciated Mozambique's
independent and non-aligned foreign policy of peace and the
government's positive endeavor in promoting regional cooperation
and safeguarding the common interests of the developing countries
in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said that despite huge efforts of the developing
countries in striving for economic growth, the gap between the
south and north kept widening and the world peace and development
are still under threat. In such a situation, China calls for
establishing just and equitable international political and
economic orders. China also holds that all countries, big or
small, should be equal and enjoy the right to choose their own
development roads according to their specific conditions.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, Li Peng and Chissano witnessed the signing of
three documents between the two governments, namely, the
agreement on economic and technical cooperation, the document on
China offering aid to Mozambique and the document on maintenance
of well drilling and water supply system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
