<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Land Nationalized Not to Be Handed Back in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government will
not hand back land nationalized during villagization to its
original owners, said Prime Minister Frederick Sumaye today.
</P>
<P>
He made the announcement at Pahi, central Tanzania when he was
informed that some few wealthy individuals were going round
claiming to be given back their plots inherited to them by their
grandfathers.
</P>
<P>
Sumaye said that original owners should clear new land and
stop bothering the people, adding that "we don't have room for
these people".
</P>
<P>
He warned that the government will not allow its people to be
enslaved in their own country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the prime minister called on Tanzanians to shift
from subsistence economy and improve their lives by increasing
production.
</P>
<P>
He said Tanzania people should get out of the present
hand-to-mouth life which has no guarantee, appealing to farmers
to expand their farms to be able to feed their families. 
</P>
</TEXT>
